 works haste out, or is my friend dead on? <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=293994">Mildane-Magelo</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/utotteswede.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TotteSwede</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 538<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/2/02 2:00:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3320.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How does haste work?</span><hr size=1> Yes, haste is a reduction of delay (or at least that´s the easiest way to look at it).<br>
Divide your base delay by (1+haste) and you´ll get the effective delay.<br>
Example: Delay 21 weapon, haste 40pct (21/(1+0.4))=15.<br>
<br>
-Fubbik- <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/utotteswede.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TotteSwede</A> at: 10/2/02 4:45:20 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/udrauk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Drauk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/2/02 5:18:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3320.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How does haste work?</span><hr size=1> Oddly EQ adds together item haste and spell haste instead <br>
of multiplying it. This means that more haste increase is based<br>
on your bacis delay instead of basic haste including previous haste.<br>
<br>
So having 21 % item haste and 20 % haste spell will result in <br>
21 % + 20 % = 41 % haste instead of 1.21 x 1.20 = 1.45  =&gt; 45 % haste.<br>
<br>
Critical damage on spells when using item crit modification and AA skill<br>
crit modification was previously calculated by multiplication, <br>
but was changed later on to work like haste so both are calculated<br>
on base nuke dmg now. So before you could crit 2.4 times base nuke dmg<br>
while now it's 2.2 times base dmg.<br>
<br>
